<TITLE> Sylhet mayor arrested in midnight raid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, May 28 (bdnews24.com)  Joint forces Monday arrested Sylhet city mayor Badruddin Ahmed Kamran in Sylhet, 20 days after he was freed on bail. He was arrested at Gulshan Hotel and Restaurant in the city at 11:55pm. Kamran's wife Asma Kamran told bdnews24.com: "I got to know he was arrested. But I don't know where he is now." Gulshan Hotel manager Shibul Chandra Das told bdnews24.com that the joint forces had arrived in three vehicles for the midnight raid. Some officers were in plainclothes, he said. Sylhet Kotwali police chief Ahmed Noor said he had heard about the arrest, without giving further details. Kamran was first arrested on April 6 in connection with the longstanding 'kitchen market' case filed in 2003. He was freed from Comilla jail on May 8. bdnews24
